fields.name: DnsServiceIP
fields.description: An IP address assigned to the Kubernetes DNS service. It must be within the Kubernetes service address range specified in serviceCidr.

fields.name: DockerBridgeCidr
fields.description: A CIDR notation IP range assigned to the Docker bridge network. It must not overlap with any Subnet IP ranges or the Kubernetes service address range.

fields.name: IPFamilies
fields.description: IP families are used to determine single-stack or dual-stack clusters. For single-stack, the expected value is IPv4. For dual-stack, the expected values are IPv4 and IPv6.

fields.name: KubeProxyConfig
fields.description: Holds configuration customizations for kube-proxy. Any values not defined will use the kube-proxy defaulting behavior. See https://v<version>.docs.kubernetes.io/docs/reference/command-line-tools-reference/kube-proxy/ where <version> is represented by a <major version>-<minor version> string. Kubernetes version 1.23 would be '1-23'.

fields.name: LoadBalancerProfile
fields.description: Profile of the cluster load balancer.

fields.name: LoadBalancerSku
fields.description: The default is 'standard'. See [Azure Load Balancer SKUs](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/load-balancer/skus) for more information about the differences between load balancer SKUs.

fields.name: NatGatewayProfile
fields.description: Profile of the cluster NAT gateway.

fields.name: NetworkDataplane
fields.description: Network dataplane used in the Kubernetes cluster.

fields.name: NetworkMode
fields.description: This cannot be specified if networkPlugin is anything other than 'azure'.

fields.name: NetworkPlugin
fields.description: Network plugin used for building the Kubernetes network.

fields.name: NetworkPluginMode
fields.description: Network plugin mode used for building the Kubernetes network.

fields.name: NetworkPolicy
fields.description: Network policy used for building the Kubernetes network.

fields.name: OutboundType
fields.description: This can only be set at cluster creation time and cannot be changed later. For more information see [egress outbound type](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/egress-outboundtype).

fields.name: PodCidr
fields.description: A CIDR notation IP range from which to assign pod IPs when kubenet is used.

fields.name: PodCidrs
fields.description: One IPv4 CIDR is expected for single-stack networking. Two CIDRs, one for each IP family (IPv4/IPv6), is expected for dual-stack networking.

fields.name: ServiceCidr
fields.description: A CIDR notation IP range from which to assign service cluster IPs. It must not overlap with any Subnet IP ranges.

fields.name: ServiceCidrs
fields.description: One IPv4 CIDR is expected for single-stack networking. Two CIDRs, one for each IP family (IPv4/IPv6), is expected for dual-stack networking. They must not overlap with any Subnet IP ranges.
